Due to the State of Emergency we are changing the presentation to a video version of our Return to Learn Plan in place of our planned FACEBOOK LIVE event.
The information shared hopefully is informative and answers a lot of questions regarding the September opening of our schools.

On Thursday, August 6th at 10am we are scheduled to have LIVE Question/Answer Town Hall, please join us. Send all questions in advance to returntolearn@roselleschools.org

As always be safe.

post_text:
We are planning our Return to Learn into the Roselle Public Schools. Learning Cohorts A/B are being developed with safety in mind.

Grades PreK to 8 are broken into Cohorts A/B. Cohort A will attend in person on Monday/Tuesday, remaining days. Cohort B will attend in person on Thursday/Friday, remaining days are virtal.

HS students will be broken into Cohorts A1/A2/B1/B2. One day in person and 4 days virtual.

All VIRTUAL LEARNING OPTIONS WILL BE AVAILABLE TO All PREK-12.

Also Family Cohorts are being developed, in which families across all grades will attend on the same day.

Our Superintendent of Schools Dr. Fisher will be conducting a Facebook Live Broadcast to share the plan and answer question.
Date:TBD
#rosellenj

In light of Governor Murphy's announcements that parents/guardians will be able to select the return to school option with which they are most comfortable, please note that we do not have a fully virtual schedule for all students. Dear Roselle Parents,

We would like to invite you to serve on our district's Return to Learn Planning Teams. We would like 5-6 parent representatives per grade span. Our grade spans are Grades Pre-K and Kindergarten, Grades 1 - 4, Grades 5-8, and Grades 9-12. Please visit www.roselleschools.org to sign up or click one of the links below for your preferred language. Parents will be selected on a first come first serve basis.

Attention RPS Community: The remote Board of Education meeting is tonight at 7 p.m.

Members of the public who wish to attend the meeting may do so by dialing 1-646-558-8656, Meeting ID: 908 298 2040, Password: 1906. The audio will also be streamed via our Facebook page.

Public comments will be accepted via email. Members of the public who wish to participate in the public comment portion of the meeting should submit comments, as well as their first name, last name and address via email to questions@roselleschools.org prior to the conclusion of the public portion of tonight's meeting.

For more information and to view tonight's agenda, please visit www.roselleschools.org. #RosellePublicSchoolsNJ

Attention RPS Community: The virtual/remote Board of Education meeting is tonight at 7 p.m.

Members of the public who wish to attend the meeting may do so by dialing 1-646-558-8656, Meeting ID: 291 400 0239, Password: 1911.

Public comments will be accepted via email. Members of the public who wish to participate in the public comment portion of the meeting should submit comments, as well as their first name, last name and address via email to questions@roselleschools.org prior to the conclusion of the public portion of tonight's meeting.

For more information, please visit www.roselleschools.org. #RosellePublicSchoolsNJ

Kindergarten Success Academy
March 27 at 7:15 PM ·

Good afternoon Parents and Students. I hope you all have been enjoying our SEL Bingo activity today in recognition of National SEL Day. Feel free to continue the activities over the weekend and share pictures. I completed an activity in all 5 domains today.
1) Took a nature walk with my son and dog.
2) Asked my family members what they are grateful for.
3) Ate a healthy salad for lunch
4) Wrote down three words my friends would use to describe me.
5) Checked in on an elderly neighbor by leaving her my contact information in case she needs anything.

post_text:
Roselle's January 2020 Students of the Month!

Last night, Interim Superintendent Dr. James Baker and the Roselle Board of Education honored outstanding students for the district’s December Students of the Month.

This month's awardees are:

Gabriel Ramirez, Roselle Preschool Annex; Diana Saget, Kindergarten Success Academy; Maximo Marin, Harrison Elementary School; Aiden Moses, Dr. Charles C. Polk Elementary School; Irene Ava Sepenu, Washington Elementary School; Sasha Kissoon, Leonard V. Moore Middle School; Alexander Cuesta, Grace Wilday Junior High School; and Michael Tennis Davis, Abraham Clark High School.

Roselle Gifted & Talented Program student Amiri B. Best, currently a fifth-grader at Leonard V. Moore Middle School, was also awarded for scoring higher than 88% of the 18,000 gifted and talented students assessed by the Johns Hopkins Center for Talented Youth in the area of mathematics last year.

Congratulations to all of our scholars! Keep making Roselle proud. #RosellePublicSchoolsNJ
